            <p>There are a few things to mention:</p>

<ul><li>The timezones are not standardized. Which means that they do not correspond with php's timezone database.</li>
<li>The avaiable localized data for timezones is not complete. Several timezones are not filled within the multiple languages.</li>
<li>Timezones differ between windows and unix or php. For example the windows timezone "africa_central" is unknown in php.</li>
<li>Localized/Normalized timezones will probably not work with Zend_Date</li>
<li>Giving the timezone for a locale could be problematic... for example the locale "en"... it would support about 20 different timezones... which to return ??</li>
<li>Also what to return if there are different supported timezones... for example within "zh_CN" or "ru_RU"</li>
</ul>
